TITLE: ‘This Is Really Scary’: Kids Struggle With Long Covid
SUMMARY: Lingering physical, mental and neurological symptoms are affecting children as well as adults, including many who had mild reactions to the initial coronavirus infection.

TITLE: Markie Post, ‘Night Court’ Actress, Dies at 70
SUMMARY: Ms. Post played a bail bondswoman on the show “The Fall Guy” in the 1980s and starred opposite John Ritter in the sitcom “Hearts Afire” in the 1990s.

SUMMARY: We hear from a few of the estimated 90 million Americans who are eligible for a Covid-19 vaccine but have chosen not to get it.

SUMMARY: In July, the continued rebound from the pandemic brings a busy month of closings.

SUMMARY: The former president scaled back the guest list for his party on Martha’s Vineyard. Who’s in and who’s out?

TITLE: For Seniors Especially, Covid Can Be Stealthy
SUMMARY: With infections increasing once more, and hospitalization rising among older adults, health experts offer a timely warning: a coronavirus infection can look different in older patients.

SUMMARY: The testimony highlights the former president’s desire to batter the Justice Department into advancing his personal agenda.
